The fresh plant has great power to cool inflammations. Spreading sores also are healed by coriander with honey or misius, likewise diseased testes, burns, carbuncles and sore ears, fluxes of the eyes too if woman's milk be added, while fluxes from belly or intestines are stayed by the seed taken in water. It is also taken in drink with rue for cholera. Intestina] parasites are expelled by cori- ander seed, taken with pomegranate juice and oil. Xenocrates records a great wonder, if it be a fact: that if women take in drink one grain of the seed the menses are retarded for one day, for two days if she takes two rrrains and so on, one day’ s delay for each grain taken. M. Varro thinks that by slightly pounded coliander and cummin, with vinegar, meat of any kind can be kept sweet in the beat of summer.
